title: Feng starts strong in Malaysia title defense
text:
Feng starts strong in Malaysia title defense Source: Shanghai Daily | October 9, 2015, Friday | Print Edition 
Feng Shanshan opened her Sime Darby LPGA Malaysia title defense in solid fashion with a 5-under-par 66 to sit one stroke off the lead after the first round yesterday. 
Alison Lee of the United States and Lin Xiyu of China shared the lead at 6-under after starting with a slew of birdies and hanging on after a three-hour rain delay disrupted play. Feng, the Chinese world No. 7, kept the pace with six birdies of her own at the Kuala Lumpur Golf and Country Club. Michelle Wie, who like Lee played a role in the United States’ emotional Solheim Cup victory over Europe last month, was also at 5-under along with Chinese Taipei’s Tseng Ya-ni and Chella Choi of South Korea. World No. 1 Park In-bee, also of South Korea, carded a 3-under 71 with three birdies on an otherwise clean card.
